---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BackgroundEffects from '../../components/BackgroundEffects.astro';

const title = 'HubSpot vs Monday CRM: Which One Fits Your Workflow?';
const description =
  'HubSpot vs Monday CRM comparison for small and mid-size teams. See where each platform wins on GTM depth, workflow flexibility, and rollout speed.';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
    <style>
      main {
        width: 100% !important;
        max-width: 940px !important;
        margin: 0 auto !important;
        padding: 7.2rem 1.4rem 3rem !important;
      }
      .hero {
        border-radius: 24px;
        padding: 2rem;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(111, 177, 252, 0.2), rgba(233, 107, 70, 0.1));
      }
      .hero h1 {
        margin: 0 0 0.8rem 0;
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        line-height: 1.08;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }
      .hero p {
        margin: 0;
        color: #d4d4d8;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }

      .section {
        margin-top: 1.25rem;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
        border-radius: 18px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
        padding: 1.2rem;
      }
      h2 {
        margin: 0 0 0.65rem 0;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
      }
      p,
      li {
        color: #d4d4d8;
      }
      .affiliate-disclosure {
        margin: 0.55rem 0 0 0;
        color: #a1a1aa;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }
      ul {
        margin: 0.7rem 0 0 1rem;
      }
      table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
      }
      th,
      td {
        padding: 0.72rem;
        text-align: left;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }
      th {
        color: #e2e8f0;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
      }
      td {
        color: #cbd5e1;
      }
      .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1rem;
      }
      .highlight {
        border: 1px solid rgba(111, 177, 252, 0.35);
        background: rgba(111, 177, 252, 0.08);
      }
      .links {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 0.8rem;
      }
      .links a {
        text-decoration: none;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 0.75rem 0.85rem;
        color: #f1f5f9;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
      }
      .links a:hover {
        border-color: rgba(111, 177, 252, 0.42);
      }

      @media (max-width: 760px) {
        main {
          padding: 6.1rem 1rem 2rem !important;
        }
        .hero {
          padding: 1.25rem;
        }
        .hero h1 {
          font-size: 1.85rem;
        }
        .grid,
        .links {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <BackgroundEffects />
    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <h1>HubSpot vs Monday CRM</h1>
        <p>
          The real choice is not feature count. It is operating model. HubSpot is stronger when you want native
          marketing-sales-service continuity. Monday CRM is stronger when your team already runs cross-functional execution
          in Monday boards and wants CRM embedded in that workflow.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Decision Matrix</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Factor</th>
              <th>HubSpot CRM</th>
              <th>Monday CRM</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Core strength</td>
              <td>Integrated GTM stack and lifecycle automation</td>
              <td>Workflow flexibility across sales + delivery operations</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Best team profile</td>
              <td>Marketing-led growth teams</td>
              <td>Ops-heavy teams with custom process needs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Implementation style</td>
              <td>Template-led, structured modules</td>
              <td>Build-your-own board and automation logic</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Cross-team visibility</td>
              <td>Strong across GTM departments</td>
              <td>Strong across GTM + project execution</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Typical friction</td>
              <td>Can feel heavy if you only need simple CRM</td>
              <td>Requires discipline to avoid over-customization</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section class="grid">
        <article class="section highlight">
          <h2>Choose HubSpot If:</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Your growth engine depends on marketing automation and lead lifecycle logic.</li>
            <li>You want a more opinionated, out-of-the-box GTM structure.</li>
            <li>You expect to expand from CRM into service and customer success workflows.</li>
          </ul>
          <p><a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/crm" target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener">Explore HubSpot CRM</a></p>
        </article>
        <article class="section">
          <h2>Choose Monday CRM If:</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>You need CRM tightly connected to execution, onboarding, or fulfillment steps.</li>
            <li>Your team values configurable pipelines, statuses, and automations.</li>
            <li>You already use Monday for project operations and want one workspace.</li>
          </ul>
          <p><a href="https://monday.com/crm" target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener">Explore Monday CRM</a></p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>4-Week Pilot Plan</h2>
        <p class="affiliate-disclosure">Disclosure: Some links above are sponsored or affiliate links. We may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Week 1: map your current sales-to-delivery handoff and recreate it in both tools.</li>
          <li>Week 2: onboard two reps and one ops stakeholder; compare daily usage consistency.</li>
          <li>Week 3: measure reporting completeness for weekly pipeline and forecast meetings.</li>
          <li>Week 4: assess admin effort per change request (new field, pipeline change, automation edit).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The winner is the platform your team updates without reminders.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Related Guides</h2>
        <div class="links">
          <a href="/crm/">CRM hub and fit tool</a>
          <a href="/crm/hubspot-vs-pipedrive/">HubSpot vs Pipedrive</a>
          <a href="/crm/best-crm-for-small-business/">Best CRM for small business</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
    <script is:inline>
      function trackEvent(eventName, params = {}) {
        if (typeof window !== 'undefined' && typeof window.gtag === 'function') {
          window.gtag('event', eventName, params);
        }
      }

      function resolveVendor(href) {
        if (href.includes('hubspot.com')) {
          return 'hubspot';
        }
        if (href.includes('monday.com')) {
          return 'monday';
        }
        return 'other';
      }

      document.querySelectorAll('a[rel~="sponsored"]').forEach((link) => {
        link.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const href = link.getAttribute('href') || '';
          trackEvent('crm_affiliate_link_click', {
            location: 'crm_hubspot_vs_monday',
            vendor: resolveVendor(href),
            link_text: (link.textContent || '').trim() || 'unknown',
          });
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
